subset_description:
### Task Description:
You are given a time series classification task with the "RacketSports" dataset. It includes data from students playing badminton or squash while wearing a smart watch, with the goal of classifying the sport and stroke type.

### Task Description:
You are given a time series classification task with the "ERing" dataset. It includes data from an electric field sensing device with six classes for thumb, index, and middle finger postures.

### Task Description:
You are given a time series classification task with the "NATOPS" dataset. It includes sensor data from the left hand tip X coordinate, with six classes representing distinct actions: 1) I have command, 2) All clear, 3) Not clear, 4) Spread wings, 5) Fold wings, 6) Lock wings.

### Task Description:
You are given a time series classification task with the "Libras" dataset. It includes 15 classes, representing hand movement types in Brazilian Sign Language.

### Task Description:
You are given a time series classification task with the "Epilepsy" dataset. It includes data collected from participants using a tri-axial accelerometer on the dominant wrist while performing 4 activities: walking, running, sawing, and seizure mimicking.

### Task Description:
You are given a time series classification task with the "PenDigits" dataset. It includes pen coordinates (x, y) of digits [0...9] drawn by 44 writers on a digital screen.
